# Autocare Stack (Canonical)

This repository is a React Native mobile app, not a web app.

## Core stack

- React Native 0.79 + Expo 53 (managed workflow)
- NativeWind (Tailwind-style utilities for React Native)
- TanStack Query v5 + openapi-fetch
- React Hook Form + `Controller` + manual validation rules
- Zustand for global state
- React Navigation v7
- i18next + react-i18next (Romanian fallback)

## Code style constraints

- Prefer `type` over `interface`
- Never use `any` unless explicitly justified
- Avoid enums, use union types or const maps
- Use async/await with try/catch
- Component files and component symbols use PascalCase
- Non-component files/folders use kebab-case
- For React components, use arrow functions
- Use single quotes for strings; use backticks only for template literals with interpolation

## Do not generate

- Next.js or web-only patterns (`'use client'`, React Router DOM, MUI)
- Apollo/GraphQL clients for API fetching
- Yup/Zod form schema validation for RHF forms
- `register()` usage on custom form inputs (use `Controller`)
- Hardcoded user-visible strings in UI
- Hardcoded hex color values when tokens exist
- Direct `fetch(url)` for app API calls

## API and data layer rules

- Use `fetchClient()` from `src/api/http-client/http-client.ts`
- Use TanStack Query hooks in domain query/mutation files
- Use query key factories per domain
- Guard nullable query params with `enabled: !!dep`

## i18n and UI

- Every user-visible string must use i18n keys
- Prefer shared UI primitives first:
  1. `src/components/ui/*`
  2. `src/components/common/*`
  3. React Native core primitives when no shared wrapper exists
- Prefer `className` with NativeWind; use `style` only for dynamic/computed styles
